data.content:
Three breaking changes in EF Core 10 affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression tree building **won't compile** anymore. The fix is dramatically simpler ŌĆö just use a regular lambda with conditionals:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Parameter` / `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` code.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one `Street` column (data corruption risk). Now EF appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). If you have an existing database, your migrations will break.

- **Nested full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** ŌĆö pin explicit column names to preserve your existing schema:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");  // was the old default
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)        // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants are redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the real executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on this interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) ŌĆö they all got the same new parameter.
